body_content.explanation: a national park (= a large area of land protected by the government because of its natural beauty or because it has a special history) in the US state of Michigan:
examples: She and two other interns worked the summer of 2018 at Isle Royale National Park, located in the northwest part of Lake Superior.
The Wenonah, a 149-passenger ferry, didn't make its usual runs from Grand Portage, Minn. to Isle Royale National Park this summer because of shallow water.
